    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"816344\">@Aaron Liu</span> Please give people the caveat if you're going to suggest <code>+native</code>. Not everyone is comfortable relying on the soundness of the compiler.</p>",
        "id": 505862036,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1742055246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"766787\">@spamegg</span> This means \"take the decision procedure, compile it, and evaluate it; it it returns 'true', then we believe the result and consider this proposition to be true\". It is not checked by the Lean kernel.</p>",
        "id": 505862113,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1742055308
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's useful if you understand the ramifications and are willing to take the risk.</p>",
        "id": 505862137,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1742055332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, is there any other way to prove this then?</p>",
        "id": 505862157,
        "sender_full_name": "spamegg",
