        "timestamp": 1742055440
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you look at the error message of <code>decide</code>, near the bottom you might be able to infer that <code>Nat.sqrt</code> failed to reduce. That happens, because it's defined using well-founded recursion.</p>\n<p>This gets around it this time:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">34</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with_unfolding_all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">decide</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 505862446,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1742055549
